(41, 6, 6, 23, 59, 16, 16, 'marvelled because of their unbelief', 'Unbelief and Wonder', 'This connection highlights the theme of wonder in response to human unbelief. Both passages emphasize a sense of astonishment at the lack of faith or intercession among people.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 6, 44, 10, 38, 38, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus'' Actions', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' active ministry as he ''went about'' teaching and doing good. Both passages emphasize his movement through villages and his healing of those in need.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 6, 24, 2, 11, 11, 'unbelief', 'Unbelief and Changing Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of unbelief and the consequences of turning away from true faith. Both passages emphasize the failure of God''s people to recognize and uphold their true glory, leading to a lack of profit in their spiritual lives.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 6, 43, 9, 30, 30, 'marvelled because of their unbelief', 'Marvelous Acts and Unbelief', 'This connection highlights the theme of marveling at miraculous acts amidst unbelief. In Mark, Jesus marvels at the unbelief of the people, while in John, the healed man points out the marvel of his healing despite the disbelief of others.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 7, 21, 4, 9, 10, 'by two and two', 'Unity in Mission and Support', 'This connection highlights the importance of companionship in both passages. Mark emphasizes sending the disciples ''by two and two,'' while Ecclesiastes underscores that ''two are better than one'' for mutual support.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 7, 40, 10, 1, 5, 'the twelve', 'Sending of the Twelve Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus calling and sending the twelve disciples. They highlight the authority given to the disciples over unclean spirits, indicating a shared mission.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 7, 42, 10, 17, 20, 'power over unclean spirits', 'Power Over Unclean Spirits', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to Jesus'' followers over evil forces. In Mark, the twelve are empowered to confront unclean spirits, while in Luke, the seventy celebrate their authority over devils through Jesus'' name.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 7, 42, 9, 1, 6, 'gave them power over unclean spirits', 'Sending of the Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of the disciples to preach and heal. They highlight the empowerment given to the disciples over unclean spirits and diseases, demonstrating a shared mission.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 7, 66, 11, 3, 3, 'gave them power', 'Connection of Power and Witnesses', 'Both passages emphasize the granting of power to individuals for a specific purpose. In Mark, the twelve are given power over unclean spirits, while in Revelation, the two witnesses are empowered to prophesy.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 7, 40, 10, 9, 14, NULL, 'Sending Forth the Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of disciples for ministry. Mark highlights the empowerment over unclean spirits, while Matthew details their instructions and the importance of their mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 7, 41, 3, 13, 14, 'send them forth', 'Sending Forth the Twelve', 'Both passages emphasize the act of sending the twelve disciples. In Mark 3:14, Jesus ordains the twelve to preach, while in Mark 6:7, he sends them forth with power over unclean spirits.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 8, 42, 9, 3, 3, 'no scrip, no bread, no money', 'Journey Instructions Comparison', 'Both passages emphasize taking nothing for the journey, highlighting a similar directive from Jesus to his disciples. The specific items mentioned, such as ''no scrip, no bread, no money,'' create a direct parallel between the two accounts.', 'parallel', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 8, 40, 10, 9, 10, 'no scrip, no bread, no money in their purse', 'Instructions for the Journey', 'Both passages emphasize the directive to take minimal provisions for the journey, highlighting reliance on God for sustenance. The mention of not taking ''scrip'' and ''money'' in both verses reinforces this theme of dependence.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 8, 42, 10, 4, 4, 'no scrip', 'Travel Instructions for Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the instruction to take minimal provisions for their journey. The directive to carry ''no scrip'' and ''no purse'' in Luke parallels the command in Mark to take ''no scrip'' and ''no money.''', 'parallel', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 8, 42, 22, 35, 35, 'no scrip, no bread, no money in their purse', 'Mission Instructions and Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the directive to travel without excess provisions, highlighting reliance on God for needs. The mention of lacking nothing in Luke reinforces the effectiveness of this command in Mark.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 9, 44, 12, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Footwear Instructions', 'Both passages emphasize the act of putting on sandals as part of preparation for action. This connection highlights the importance of being ready to follow divine instruction.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 9, 49, 6, 15, 15, 'be shod with sandals', 'Connection of Footwear Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being prepared. In Mark, the instruction to be ''shod with sandals'' relates to readiness, while Ephesians speaks of being ''shod with the preparation of the gospel of peace.'' This connection highlights the theme of readiness for mission.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 10, 40, 10, 11, 13, 'there abide till ye depart', 'Instructions for Hospitality', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of finding a worthy house to stay in and remaining there until departure. This connection highlights the shared directive to abide in a place that is deemed suitable for the disciples'' mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
