(41, 6, 11, 44, 18, 6, 6, 'shake off the dust under your feet', 'Rejection and Accountability', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of rejection. In Mark, shaking off dust signifies a testimony against those who do not receive the message, while in Acts, shaking the raiment indicates a similar accountability for those opposing the message.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 11, 16, 5, 13, 13, 'shake off the dust under your feet', 'Judgment and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability in both passages. Mark 6:11 speaks of judgment for those who reject the message, while Nehemiah 5:13 emphasizes consequences for failing to uphold promises.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 11, 42, 10, 10, 15, 'more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrha', 'Judgment and Rejection of Cities', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of rejecting the messengers of God, specifically mentioning the act of shaking off dust as a testimony against the cities. They also highlight the comparison of judgment for these cities to that of Sodom and Gomorrha, indicating a severe warning for unrepentant cities.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
